AI Education! •
-
Last week, we had the privilege of presenting to the student body at Westmount Charter School.
-
Our presentation covered AI topics such as how large language models work, effective prompting techniques, and the evolving role of AI in academia.
-
We would like to thank @wcsmidhigh_official for hosting us and supporting SAIL’s mission of providing zero-cost comprehensive AI education to the general public.

Here are some highlights from a gorgeous Tuesday group rides a couple weeks ago! We're excited for our Tuesday night group ride tonight, meeting at Bikechain at 6pm today for a 6:15 roll-out! Come join us!

We're doing a 16 km loop up to Oriole Park and back through the ravine system. The weather is expected to hold clear enough :) Can't wait!

🐞 Come join us on a 15 km group ride to Oriole Park on Tuesday, July 9! We'll follow a beautiful loop with some fun hills, enjoy the park, and coast through the Cedarvale and Nordheimer ravines.

🐝 Meet at Bikechain (230 College, entrance on Huron) at 6 pm, roll-out at ​6:15 pm. BYO bike, water, and sun protection. This will be a talking pace, no-drop ride open to all cyclists! We'll return to Bikechain around 7:45 pm. We'll bring light snacks.

🦗 If you'd like to meet us there or along the way, please get in touch. Can't make this one? Don't worry, we'll be riding to a different location every Tuesday and most weekends until the end of the season!

🌉Come join us on a 22 km group ride to Humber Bay Arch Bridge tomorrow! Take in the breathtaking futuristic architecture and refreshing lake breeze. 

🌊Meet at Bikechain at 6 pm, roll-out at ​6:15 pm. BYO bike, water, and sun protection. We'll bring light snacks. This will be a talking pace, no-drop ride open to all cyclists! We'll return to Bikechain around 8:45 pm. 

😥 If you'd like to meet us there or along the way, please get in touch. Can't make this one? Don't worry, we'll be riding to a different location every Tuesday and most weekends until the end of the season!

🗻 Come join us on a group ride to Bluffer's Park Beach on Sunday, June 23! One one of the longest days of the year, we're taking in the sun next to the cathedral bluffs and fine sandy shores. This will be a gorgeous 45 km round trip on the Martin Goodman trail, throguh Woodbine beach, along the Waterfront trail, and back through Taylor Creek, the Don Ravine and Rosedale Valley!

⛱ Meet at Bikechain at 12 pm for a 12:15 pm roll-out. BYO bike, water, and sun protection. We'll bring light snacks. We're riding at a talking pace, all cyclists welcome! We'll return to Bikechain around ​4 pm.

😢 If you'd like to meet us there or along the way, please get in touch. Can't make this one? Don't worry, we'll be riding to a different location every Tuesday and most weekends until the end of the season!

🌉 Come join us on a 22 km group ride to Humber Bay Arch Bridge on Tuesday, June 25! Take in the breathtaking futuristic architecture and refreshing lake breeze. 

🌊 Meet at Bikechain at 6 pm, roll-out at ​6:15 pm. BYO bike, water, and sun protection. We'll bring light snacks. This will be a talking pace, no-drop ride open to all cyclists! We'll return to Bikechain around 8:45 pm.

As BSA-UTSG’s 2023-2024 journey comes to a close, we look back on yet another year filled with loads of joy, memories, and meaningful contribution to our community. We are extemely grateful to our dedicated team of executives and associates and to our patrons and collaborators — your support made it all happen. We hope you had as much fun as we did! 🎉🥳
